1
00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:01.090
- [Narrator] To get the most out of this course

2
00:00:01.090 --> 00:00:04.020
I recommend a few things to get you started.

3
00:00:04.020 --> 00:00:06.040
It would be very good to have a hands on

4
00:00:06.040 --> 00:00:08.070
with the fundaments of core Java APIs

5
00:00:08.070 --> 00:00:10.080
as we call Java standard editions.

6
00:00:10.080 --> 00:00:13.000
It would be very good to have a good hands-on

7
00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:15.040
with the Java Database Connectivity API

8
00:00:15.040 --> 00:00:18.040
which is used to transact against the database.

9
00:00:18.040 --> 00:00:21.080
Then, any usage of IDE that is integrated

10
00:00:21.080 --> 00:00:24.000
in a developing environment by Eclipse,

11
00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:27.020
Netbeans, Intelligio, or any other would do.

12
00:00:27.020 --> 00:00:30.020
A basic hands on of databases would be necessary

13
00:00:30.020 --> 00:00:31.090
because we are going to build an application

14
00:00:31.090 --> 00:00:34.030
which is going to converse with the database.

15
00:00:34.030 --> 00:00:38.020
And lastly, we need to display pages on the browser,

16
00:00:38.020 --> 00:00:40.060
which means there will be HTML and CSS code

17
00:00:40.060 --> 00:00:41.070
in all those pages.

18
00:00:41.070 --> 00:00:45.070
So an acquaintance of that is really going to be helpful.

19
00:00:45.070 --> 00:00:47.050
There are a few terminologies that we may need

20
00:00:47.050 --> 00:00:48.080
to use as a part of this course.

21
00:00:48.080 --> 00:00:50.040
The first one is API,

22
00:00:50.040 --> 00:00:52.030
which is application programming interface

23
00:00:52.030 --> 00:00:55.080
so any class, any method that we refer

24
00:00:55.080 --> 00:00:57.040
from the Java Standard Edition

25
00:00:57.040 --> 00:01:00.090
or Java Enterprise Edition forms an API.

26
00:01:00.090 --> 00:01:03.090
The next one is JAR, which is Java Archive,

27
00:01:03.090 --> 00:01:06.030
which is basically a bundle of class files

28
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:08.080
that are external to your project.

29
00:01:08.080 --> 00:01:10.000
You may need to include them

30
00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:12.010
in the built part of your project.

31
00:01:12.010 --> 00:01:15.000
Build path, on the other hand, or as we say class path,

32
00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:17.050
is the location of all the user refined classes

33
00:01:17.050 --> 00:01:19.060
that you have used in your web application

34
00:01:19.060 --> 00:01:21.010
so that your compiler finds them

35
00:01:21.010 --> 00:01:25.020
and appropriately uses them when it wants to run your app.

36
